snippet.textDisplay:
First off, they were flying VFR in Class D airspace. The flight was doable until they ran into IMC conditions. If the pilot were IFR rated we wouldn't be talking about this.
Kobe's helicopter wasn't equipped with TAWS crash alert system, had no Black-Box nor flight or voice recorder and no live avionics equipment nor HUD system.
These basic instruments would have saved their lives. Period!
But what kills me is, why didn't the pilot just slow down to a almost stop, descend the hopper and find a safe place to set it down until the weather changed???
Instead we have people dead and lives destroyed!
RIP Kobe and the rest of the victims.
#Sad

snippet.textDisplay:
Meanwhile in Heaven, Paul Walker drives and sees Kobe and GiGi

Paul: *Kobe! GiGi! There’s some
People that heard you arrived here and wanna play a game a ball with you*

Kobe: Oh really, now? He knows who he playin against right?
Paul: Oh he knows and he wants GiGi to play too
GiGi: Oh daddy I feel sorry them!
Paul: Hop in and I’ll show you

As they drive through the clouds they arrive to a golden gate and inside was a white and good basketball court with a 24/2 /9 logo mid court honoring Heavens new residents, Kobe, GiGi and the 7 souls who lost their lives in the crash. While all the fans and stars that once passed, they all stood and gave Kobe a standing ovation chanting his name, then as the crowd calmed, he heard a ball bounce and heard a deep but subtle voice

You ready to play some basketball Kobe Bryant?

When Kobe and GiGi turned around, their smiles shined brighter than than the sun when Prince himself stood in the middle of the court spinning the ball in his finger and along side him..none other than Charlie Murphy.

Prince: What do you say Kobe? You and Mambacita vs me and Charlie Murphy?

Kobe: You wanna piece of the Mamba? GiGi they ain’t ready!
GiGi They don’t want the smoke daddy
Charlie: Yall gon be eating pancakes 🥞 when we done witcha!
Kobe: Lets ball

The crowd goes wild as everything fades into the bright white light.
